<title>JAPAN: HIKARI TSUSHIN TO BUY STAKE IN INFORMATION FIRM.</title>
<headline>HIKARI TSUSHIN TO BUY STAKE IN INFORMATION FIRM.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1997-08-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Japanese phone service company Hikari Tsushin Inc said on Friday it would acquire an 18.39 percent stake in an information equipment firm.  </p>
<p>Hikari Tsushin said in a statement that it would buy Sofmap Co Ltd's stake for three billion yen.</p>
<p>Sofmap, which sells new and used personal computers, software and other information equipment, is expected to issue 317,000 new shares on August 26, the statement said.</p>
